<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-04-30T18:40:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-04-30T18:40:00-05:00" n="293" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d293">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 839.00/1194.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Sullivan</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>
                                    <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Santo Domingo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-04-30T19:00:00-04:40">
                                    <hi rend="italic">April 30, 1914, 7 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Revolutionists by resistance have caused closing of Puerto Plata
                            customhouses and interference with American Government’s rights under
                            the convention, which provides that we may protest the same. I earnestly
                            recommend Department’s serious consideration of this phase of present
                            insurrection.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Sullivan</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>